duties_responsibilities.duty: Provide counseling and therapy services for individuals, couples, and families, both in-person and via telehealth.
Supervise and mentor associate level licensed practitioners in clinical practice and professional development.
Manage private practice operations, including billing/insurance, credentialing, and electronic records.
Offer specialized therapy services such as EMDR, Couples/Relationship Therapy, and other certifications.
Participate in clinical consultation, contribute to the team, and maintain quality care standards for clients.

education_certification.credential: Licensed (or license eligible) LCSW, LPC, LMFT, or licensed Psychologist in Georgia.
Master's degree in Psychology, Counseling, Social Work, or related field.
